      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics assumptions (linear elasticity for titanium alloy, frictional contact at screw-rod interface) justified by literature and sensitivity analysis showing less than 3% QoI sensitivity to plasticity model parameters within expected strain range.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) remains nominally elastic below yield under ASTM F1717 loading conditions. Sensitivity study confirmed that incorporating bilinear isotropic hardening changed predicted stiffness by less than 1.5%. Frictional contact coefficient varied ±50%; QoI sensitivity 2.1%. Model form uncertainty quantified and within required bounds."
