      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from MMPDS-12 for Ti-6Al-4V; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of as-manufactured specimens with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and Poisson ratio (0.342) taken from MMPDS-12 handbook values. CMM measurements of screw and rod geometry performed on three representative specimens; dimensional deviations from nominal less than 0.05 mm. Input uncertainty propagated through Latin Hypercube sampling (N=200 runs); QoI uncertainty contribution from inputs less than 3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances; material certification records available.",
      "rationale": "Eleven constructs assembled from production-representative components. Dimensional inspection via CMM confirmed all critical dimensions within drawing tolerances. Material certifications (mill certs) available for all metallic components. Sample representativeness judged adequate for Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions should span at least two load levels or two fixture configurations to characterize model behavior across the relevant operating envelope; inter-laboratory reproducibility coefficient of variation below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single prescribed load configuration per ASTM F1717 protocol. While inter-laboratory reproducibility was confirmed (CV = 3.8% across two labs), only one test condition was explored. The required Gradation 3 for this factor — which demands multi-condition coverage to bound the model's predictive envelope — was not achieved. Achieved level remains Gradation 2. This shortfall was acknowledged by the assessment team but judged acceptable given the standardized nature of the F1717 protocol and the consistency of results across laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions and loading replicate experimental fixture geometry and load application point within 1 mm; torque preload on set screw represented by equivalent contact pressure.",
      "rationale": "Fixture geometry digitized from engineering drawings and confirmed against physical fixture measurements. Load application point matched to within 0.3 mm. Set screw torque preload (4 Nm) converted to equivalent contact pressure using Hertzian contact approximation and verified against strain gauge measurements on instrumented constructs. Equivalency of inputs confirmed at required level."
    },
    {
