      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly map to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the vertebral column; yield force defines the onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs are explicitly required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw submissions. Relevance confirmed at required level."
    },
